reviewText: A little slow but good movie!
One of my favorite movies, I bought this copy for my Mom.
This is a great movie filmed in Ft Worth Texas on a low budget.  Definitely worth the watch!
Great movie you probably never heard of.
One of my favorite independents.  I have been impressed with Staphanies transformation in this film, always a favorite concept,  she does it well.

This is an excellent noir indie film. It's very observant & deceptively simple, throwing the audience a few curves along the way. The process of securing a fake ID is probably very different today, but was reasonable at the time of release. This is a 3 1/2~star movie, but Amazon isn't giving me the 1/2 star option.
